 <appendix xml:id="debugger" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
  <title>Debugging in HHVM</title>

  <sect1 xml:id="debugger.about">
   <title>About debugging in HHVM</title>
   <para>
    HHVM has a debugger called <literal>hphpd</literal> that is can be used to debug a running program or used as a standalone line-by-line scratch pad for simple testing. Invoke <literal>hphpd</literal> by typing the following at the command line:
    <informalexample>
      <programlisting role="bash">
<![CDATA[
hhvm -m debug [filename]
]]>
      </programlisting>
      <note>
        <para>
          <literal>filename</literal> is not needed if you want to run the debugger in a "standalone" format for quick testing.
        </para>
      </note>
    </informalexample>
   </para>
   <para>
    For more information on the debugger see <link xlink:href="https://github.com/facebook/hhvm/blob/master/hphp/doc/debugger.start">GitHub</link>.
   </para>
  </sect1>

 </appendix>

